# Waste-to-Energy-Initiative
Energy Policy Institute at the University of Chicago (EPIC) in collaboration with Gandipet Welfare Society

During my summer internship, I contributed to a Waste-to-Energy initiative focused on sustainable waste management and clean energy solutions in Hyderabad, India. My work combined technical research with stakeholder engagement, supporting project implementation and collaboration between community organizations and external partners.

# My responsibilities included:

Supporting research on Waste-to-Energy technologies and sustainable waste management practices.
Assisting in project coordination and implementation.
Engaging with local communities through workshops and awareness activities.
Collaborating with partner organizations and stakeholders to strengthen project outreach and identify opportunities for future expansion.

This experience strengthened my understanding of environmental policy implementation, project management, and multi-stakeholder collaboration while demonstrating how research can support practical sustainability initiatives.

